text: Apparently someone told all the hipsters about edinborough castle.  At least the pints are still as good as ever.
@natenash203 Nice!  Hope you can get some Crossfit in while you're out here!
A fresh pint of lambic.... That's the stuff!
@kdoll Yea, all is well.  Bouncing back already.
Ouch.  That sucked.
"Every second counts", the Crossfit movie, is awesome. Get it!
This day just got very, very interesting.  Big changes afoot!
Just picked up tix to the The Tragically Hip show at the Fillmore.  My favorite band, at my favorite venue, in my favorite city.  Priceless.
To remind me of days where TVs sat on the floor, surrounded by wooden cabinets, my LCD monitor has a ghost of the GMail logo burned into it.
"Always a student", new post about the pursuit of learning.  http://bit.ly/17NYTn
Really sad news about the death of Jay Bennett.  Listening to old Wilco today.
Plumbing issue fixed, thanks to what the hardware store clerk called "a giant plumbing dildo".  Thanks man, my pipes appreciated it.
No matter how long you've owned a house, weekend visits to the hardware store persist.  I find myself in need of a plumbing snake.  Sweet.
Reading "On Writing Well" (http://bit.ly/3ROfd), realizing that you could easily mistake this for a book on programming heuristics.
@abie similarly, Marin is sunny, warm and relaxed as is our weekend tradition, holiday or not. Come north! Muir Beach is usually a good call
Even the way my son eats an apple reveals his inner carnivour.
I see the same couple going to church every weekend on my way to the coffee shop. Maybe we're both going for the same reasons.
Just watched "21 Grams".  I can't recall a more intense and emotionally raw movie.
Just upgraded my Dell Mini 9 Netbook to OS X 10.5.7.  Now getting 4+ hours of battery life.  I LOVE this thing!
@jamis Congratulations!  Impressive you were able to hold out and be surprised on the big day!
So excited that the Crossfit movie "Every Second Counts" is finally released.  Grab a copy and get inspired: everysecondcounts-themovie.com
It'd be nice to see ruby-toolbox.com use traffic stats in addition to github watchers and forks.  cruisecontrol.rb looks too low for example
Listening to Krasny talk over Eric Idle on Forum (NPR), realizing @abie was right.  I'm a Krasny apologist no more!
Some of my most favorite conversations are with cab drivers.  Love the random topics they've been noodling on during their shift.
Inbox zero is very addicting.  Been at zero on all mail accounts for almost 24 hours now.  Time for a calendar about nothing to track it? :)
@peterc zsh tries to be too smart for me.  "smart auto correction" is a pain, and i can't grok the scripts, like tab completion, etc.
After using zsh and emacs since January, I'm ready to leave them both.  I still feel more comfortable and can GTD faster in bash and vim.
@abie btw, I'll be back in SF on tuesday with your program!
@abie I usually get raw cashews at Trader Joe's.  Check out newurbanfarms.com, I just got a huge order of raw macadamia's.  Most excellent!

Just signed up crossfitafrica.com to statulo.us!  Building the community by word of mouth alone has been a really fun part of this project.
First day out with my @exceptional shirt on.  Thanks, @eoghanmccabe, everybody I've met wants to get exceptional :)

Have met some really passionate and interesting people in the last few days, all working on cool projects.
